data.title: Manne Siegbahn Nobel Prize Physics 1924 X-Ray Spectroscopy Signed Photograph
data.meta_description: Karl Manne Georg Siegbahn [1886 1978] was a Swedish physicist who was awarded the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1924 for his discoveries and research in the field of X-ray spectroscopy. The photograph is a formal image signed "Manne Siegbahn" and dated 1967" in blue ink.
